    • Method Detail

      • visit

        public com.github.javaparser.ast.Node visit​(com.github.javaparser.ast.stmt.SynchronizedStmt ss,
                                            java.lang.Void arg)
        A method which walks through all the synchronized statements in the compilation unit. If the synchronized statement has a parent synchronized statement with a different lock, the lock objects are swapped between the synchronized statement The line reference and method name of the synchronized statement mutant is set in the MutationModifier superclass. If the current synchronized statement is not marked for mutation, no action is performed and the mutationsVisited value of the MutationModifier superclass is incremented.
        Specified by:
        visit in interface com.github.javaparser.ast.visitor.GenericVisitor<com.github.javaparser.ast.visitor.Visitable,​java.lang.Void>
        Overrides:
        visit in class com.github.javaparser.ast.visitor.ModifierVisitor<java.lang.Void>
        Parameters:
        ss - - the current synchronized statement
        arg - - always null
        Returns:
        - the synchronized statement with any modifications applied
